    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the nuance part, but it feels like the \"pro\" side always focuses on these big abstract ideas like \"local spending\" while the \"con\" side is dealing with the actual reality of paying rent and staff next month. do you think the argument that it helps the economy is actually backed by much solid evidence, or is it more of a theoretical thing that doesn't really hold up for a single small shop owner?",
